text: Jane on her Own is the fourth book in a series of four American children's picture books written by Ursula K. Le Guin. S. D. Schindler made the pictures. Scholastic published the book in 1999. It tells the stories of kittens who were born with wings. Category:American children's books Category:Books by Ursula K. Le Guin Category:1999 books
title: Jane on her Own
